Areas to Check
Color Contrast

Ensure that the colors defined in :root provide enough contrast against each other. For instance, --primary-color is dark, while the body text color is #682a93, which is a shade of purple. If these colors are too close in value, it could cause readability issues.
Background Colors

If any elements have backgrounds or overlays with low opacity (like --primary-color2 or --primary-color3), they might cause readability issues when placed behind text. Ensure that these colors are used appropriately and don't affect text visibility.
CSS Resets

The universal reset (* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; }) is fine, but it might interact with other styles if not properly managed. Make sure that other components and their styles don’t override or conflict with these global styles.
