The .error class includes an animation that shakes the element horizontally. While this won’t directly affect color or visibility, ensure that this animation is applied intentionally and doesn’t overlap or interfere with other text.
Debugging Steps
Check Text Contrast

Verify that text colors have sufficient contrast against their backgrounds. You can use tools like the WebAIM Contrast Checker to test this.
Inspect Elements

Use the browser’s developer tools to inspect elements and see the computed styles and background colors. This can help you understand how different styles are interacting.
Verify Backgrounds

Ensure that background colors with opacity (like --primary-color2 or --primary-color3) are used where they are intended and do not overlap in a way that reduces text readability.
Test Without Global Styles

Temporarily remove or comment out the global styles to see if the issue persists. This can help isolate whether the problem is related to global styles or something else in your application.
